Definition at line 66 of file hs_msgdefs.h.

#define HS_DISABLE_ALIVENESS_CC   7
Name:
Disable Aliveness Indicator
Description
Disables the Aliveness Indicator UART output
Command Mnemonic(s):
$sc_$cpu_HS_DisableCPUAlive
Command Structure
HS_NoArgsCmd_t
Command Verification
Successful execution of this command may be verified with the following telemetry:
  • $sc_$cpu_HS_CMDPC - command counter will increment
  • $sc_$cpu_HS_CPUAliveState - will be set to Disabled
  • The HS_DISABLE_ALIVENESS_DBG_EID informational event message will be generated when the command is executed
Error Conditions
This command may fail for the following reason(s):
  • Command packet length not as expected
Evidence of failure may be found in the following telemetry:
  • $sc_$cpu_HS_CMDEC - command error counter will increment
  • Error specific event message HS_LEN_ERR_EID
Criticality
None
See also:
HS_ENABLE_ALIVENESS_CC

#define HS_RESET_CC   1
Name:
Reset Counters
Description
Resets the HS housekeeping counters
Command Mnemonic(s):
$sc_$cpu_HS_ResetCtrs
Command Structure
HS_NoArgsCmd_t
Command Verification
Successful execution of this command may be verified with the following telemetry:
  • $sc_$cpu_HS_CMDPC - command counter will be cleared
  • $sc_$cpu_HS_CMDEC - command error counter will be cleared
  • $sc_$cpu_HS_EVTMonCnt - events monitored counter will be cleared
  • The HS_RESET_DBG_EID debug event message will be generated when the command is executed
Error Conditions
This command may fail for the following reason(s):
  • Command packet length not as expected
Evidence of failure may be found in the following telemetry:
  • $sc_$cpu_HS_CMDEC - command error counter will increment
  • Error specific event message HS_LEN_ERR_EID
Criticality
None
See also:
